Place cabbage, jicama, and apple in a large bowl and toss to combine. Whisk mayonnaise, pineapple juice, sugar, hot sauce, salt, and pepper in a bowl until mixture is smooth and fluffy, 1 to 2 minutes. Pour mayonnaise mixture over cabbage, jicama, and apple; toss to combine. Let sit for 5 minutes. Mix in cilantro and toss again. Garnish with toasted corn bits and serve immediately.